entries.title: Lost Opportunities (Thursday Crossword, June 6)

entries.description: Some demonstrations are persisting at American universities as school year winds down.

entries.title: Former Sustainable Fuel Startup CEO Sentenced for Embezzlement

entries.title: Mexican Peso Sentiment is Neutral Not Bearish, Morgan Stanley Says
entries.description: Mexico’s peso was recovering after a selloff following Sunday’s overwhelming ruling party election win.

entries.title: The Unspoken Rules of Hotel Pool Etiquette, According to a Seasoned Pro

entries.title: New York Gov. Kathy Hochul Abruptly Halts Manhattan Congestion Pricing
entries.description: The plan to charge drivers $15 to enter the city was set to take effect later this month.

entries.title: Nvidia Hits $3 Trillion Market Cap

entries.description: Shane Hostetter will join the chemical company next month from Quaker Houghton. His appointment follows the suspension of three Chemours leaders early this year.

entries.title: U.S. Natural Gas Futures Rebound on Weather Outlook
entries.description: U.S. natural gas futures continued on their roller-coaster ride, bouncing back from the previous day’s selloff to recover Monday’s levels.

entries.title: 'You Don't Land Softly'
entries.description: Honoring and remembering on the 80th anniversary of D-Day.

entries.title: Rubio's Restaurants Files for Bankruptcy With Plans to Sell Chain

entries.title: Psychiatrist Henry Jarecki Says Relationship With Epstein Accuser Was Consensual

entries.title: This Summer's Best Iced Teas Come in Bright Colors and Bold Flavors

entries.title: Virginia Passed a Law Adopting California's EV Standards. Now It Wants Out.
